    <item>
      <title>Multiple Sourcing of Imported Intermediate Inputs</title>
      <link>https://rtbrt7.github.io/project/project3/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://rtbrt7.github.io/project/project3/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;This is a &lt;span style=&#34;color:#D4AF37&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;work in progress&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are exploring why do manufacturing firms import intermediate inputs from multiple suppliers (even when the quality of the imported inputs remains the same)? Are they optimizing the hold-up problem, or are they diversifying risk? Is it dependent on the type of inputs they are importing? We found strong evidence of (product dependent) multiple sourcing even for small single-product firms from the Chinese Customs Data.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
